  'sleep_disorder_reset',
  12,
  'Releasing Hidden Stress',
  'Day 12 - Releasing Hidden Stress',
  '',
  18,
  '[{"type":"intro","dayNumber":12,"dayTitle":"Releasing Hidden Stress","goal":"Complete Day 12 with steady, consistent action.","estimatedMinutes":18},{"type":"lesson","title":"Today''s Focus","paragraphs":["Complete Day 12 with steady, consistent action."],"highlight":"Consistency compounds into long-term change."},{"type":"action_step","stepNumber":1,"title":"Morning Sunlight Exposure (10–20 Minutes)","instructions":["Within 30 minutes of waking, go outside and expose your eyes to natural daylight.","Step outside your home, balcony, or street.","Do not wear sunglasses.","Face the direction of the sky (not directly at the sun).","Stay outside for 10–20 minutes.","Try walking slowly during sunlight exposure to strengthen your circadian rhythm signal.","Why this works","Morning sunlight resets the brain’s internal clock, helping regulate melatonin production at night."],"whyThisWorks":"Small consistent actions reinforce stability and reduce automatic, stress-driven reactions."},{"type":"breathing_exercise","title":"Hydration + Nervous System Activation","instructions":"Immediately after sunlight, drink 500–700 ml of water. Then perform this breathing exercise. 10 Cycles of Physiological Sigh Inhale through nose Take a second short inhale Slowly exhale through mouth Repeat 10 times. This lowers stress hormones and calms the nervous system.","pattern":{"inhaleSeconds":4,"exhaleSeconds":6},"cycles":10},{"type":"exercise_routine","title":"Increased Morning Movement (sleep Pressure Builder)","exercises":[{"name":"Total Movement Time: 25–30 Minutes","instructions":["Perform with steady breathing and controlled pacing."]},{"name":"Exercise Routine","instructions":["Perform with steady breathing and controlled pacing."]},{"name":"Brisk Walking","instructions":["Perform with steady breathing and controlled pacing."]},{"name":"15 Minutes Continuous Walking.","instructions":["Perform with steady breathing and controlled pacing."]},{"name":"Bodyweight Squats","instructions":["Perform with steady breathing and controlled pacing."]},{"name":"20 Reps × 5 Sets","instructions":["Perform with steady breathing and controlled pacing."]},{"name":"Pushups","instructions":["Perform with steady breathing and controlled pacing."]},{"name":"15 Reps × 4 Sets","instructions":["Perform with steady breathing and controlled pacing."]},{"name":"Jumping Jacks","instructions":["Perform with steady breathing and controlled pacing."]},{"name":"30 Reps × 4 Sets","instructions":["Perform with steady breathing and controlled pacing."]},{"name":"Standing Forward Stretch","instructions":["Perform with steady breathing and controlled pacing."]},{"name":"12 Slow Repetitions","instructions":["Perform with steady breathing and controlled pacing."]}]},{"type":"action_step","stepNumber":2,"title":"Caffeine Control Rule","instructions":["Follow this rule strictly:","No caffeine after 2 PM","This includes:","coffee","tea","energy drinks","pre-workout drinks","Caffeine can remain active in the body 6–8 hours, disturbing sleep quality."],"whyThisWorks":"Small consistent actions reinforce stability and reduce automatic, stress-driven reactions."},{"type":"mindfulness_exercise","title":"Evening Nervous System Downshift","steps":["About 60 minutes before bed, listen to your guided sleep meditation audio.","Lie comfortably in bed.","Play the meditation audio at low volume.","Close your eyes and follow the instructions.","Allow the body to relax naturally.","Recommended length: 10–20 minutes."],"completionMessage":"Stay with the practice until your body and mind feel steadier."},{"type":"mindfulness_exercise","title":"Body Temperature Sleep Trick","steps":["Take a warm shower 60–90 minutes before sleep.","Why this works","After the shower, your body temperature drops slightly, which signals the brain that it is time to","sleep."],"completionMessage":"Stay with the practice until your body and mind feel steadier."},{"type":"mindfulness_exercise","title":"The Military Sleep Method (fast Sleep Technique)","steps":["Once in bed, do this:","Relax your forehead","Relax jaw and tongue","Drop shoulders completely","Slowly breathe out","Then imagine a calm scene:","You are lying beside a quiet waterfall in a peaceful forest.","The sound of water is gentle and calming.","Focus on the sound and the calm scene while breathing slowly.","Day 12 Sleep Trick – The “Gratitude Reset”","Stress and negative thoughts often stay active in the brain before sleep.","About 20–30 minutes before bed, write down 3 things you are grateful for today.","They can be small things:","a good conversation","a nice meal","a peaceful moment during the day","Take a moment to mentally relive each moment.","Why this works","Gratitude shifts the brain away from stress and problem-solving mode.","This activates emotional calm and prepares the brain for relaxed sleep.","Day 12 Goal","Reduce mental stress before sleep, allowing the brain to transition more easily into sleep.","By Day 12 many people begin noticing:","calmer thoughts at night","deeper emotional relaxation","smoother transition into sleep"],"completionMessage":"Stay with the practice until your body and mind feel steadier."},{"type":"journal","prompt":"What helped you most on Day 12?","helperText":"Write one or two practical observations.","followUpPrompt":"What will you repeat tomorrow?"},{"type":"close","message":"Day 12 is complete.","secondaryMessage":"You reinforced releasing hidden stress today."}]'::jsonb
)
