 Technique)","steps":["Once in bed, do this:","Relax your forehead","Relax jaw and tongue","Drop shoulders completely","Slowly breathe out","Then imagine a calm scene:","You are lying beside a quiet lake surrounded by mountains.","The water is still and the night sky is full of stars.","Focus on the calm scene while breathing slowly.","Day 13 Sleep Trick – The “Slow Blink Relaxation”","This trick helps relax the visual system and brain activity, which can keep people awake.","While lying in bed:","Close your eyes gently.","Slowly open them halfway.","Slowly close them again.","Repeat this 8–10 times slowly.","Why this works","Slow blinking relaxes the eye muscles and brain alertness system, helping the body transition into","sleep mode.","It mimics the natural blinking pattern that happens right before falling asleep.","Day 13 Goal","Encourage deep physical relaxation and nervous system calm, helping the body transition more","easily into deep sleep stages.","By Day 13 many people begin noticing:","deeper sleep cycles","less physical tension at night","feeling more refreshed in the morning"],"completionMessage":"Stay with the practice until your body and mind feel steadier."},{"type":"journal","prompt":"What helped you most on Day 13?","helperText":"Write one or two practical observations.","followUpPrompt":"What will you repeat tomorrow?"},{"type":"close","message":"Day 13 is complete.","secondaryMessage":"You reinforced deep body relaxation today."}]'::jsonb
)
