d controlled pacing."]},{"name":"25 Reps × 5 Sets","instructions":["Perform with steady breathing and controlled pacing."]},{"name":"Pushups","instructions":["Perform with steady breathing and controlled pacing."]},{"name":"20 Reps × 5 Sets","instructions":["Perform with steady breathing and controlled pacing."]},{"name":"Jumping Jacks","instructions":["Perform with steady breathing and controlled pacing."]},{"name":"50 Reps × 4 Sets","instructions":["Perform with steady breathing and controlled pacing."]},{"name":"Plank Hold","instructions":["Perform with steady breathing and controlled pacing."]},{"name":"45 Seconds × 4 Sets","instructions":["Perform with steady breathing and controlled pacing."]}]},{"type":"action_step","stepNumber":2,"title":"Caffeine Control Rule","instructions":["Follow this rule strictly:","No caffeine after 2 PM","This includes:","coffee","tea","energy drinks","pre-workout drinks","Caffeine can remain active in the body 6–8 hours, interfering with sleep cycles."],"whyThisWorks":"Small consistent actions reinforce stability and reduce automatic, stress-driven reactions."},{"type":"mindfulness_exercise","title":"Evening Nervous System Downshift","steps":["About 60 minutes before bed, listen to your guided sleep meditation audio.","Lie comfortably in bed.","Play the meditation audio at low volume.","Close your eyes and follow the instructions.","Allow your body to relax naturally.","Recommended length: 10–20 minutes."],"completionMessage":"Stay with the practice until your body and mind feel steadier."},{"type":"mindfulness_exercise","title":"Body Temperature Sleep Trick","steps":["Take a warm shower 60–90 minutes before sleep.","Why this works","After the shower, the body temperature naturally drops, signaling the brain that it is time to sleep."],"completionMessage":"Stay with the practice until your body and mind feel steadier."},{"type":"mindfulness_exercise","title":"The Military Sleep Method (fast Sleep Technique)","steps":["Once in bed, do this:","Relax your forehead","Relax jaw and tongue","Drop shoulders completely","Slowly breathe out","Then imagine a calm scene:","You are lying in a quiet forest clearing under the moonlight.","The air is cool and peaceful.","Everything around you is calm and silent.","Focus on the calm scene while breathing slowly.","Day 17 Sleep Trick – The “Foot Massage Relaxation”","The feet contain many nerve endings connected to the nervous system.","Relaxing them before bed can help the entire body relax.","Before sleeping:","Sit comfortably on the bed.","Gently massage the bottom of each foot.","Apply light pressure using your thumbs.","Massage for 2–3 minutes per foot.","Why this works","Foot massage stimulates relaxation pathways in the nervous system, reducing physical tension and","helping the body transition into sleep.","Day 17 Goal","Encourage deep physical relaxation and nervous system calm, helping the body enter deeper","restorative sleep cycles.","By Day 17 many people notice:","deeper sleep","fewer awakenings during the night","waking up feeling more refreshed"],"completionMessage":"Stay with the practice until your body and mind feel steadier."},{"type":"journal","prompt":"What helped you most on Day 17?","helperText":"Write one or two practical observations.","followUpPrompt":"What will you repeat tomorrow?"},{"type":"close","message":"Day 17 is complete.","secondaryMessage":"You reinforced deep nervous system recovery today."}]'::jsonb
)
