ce in bed, do this:","Relax your forehead","Relax jaw and tongue","Drop shoulders completely","Slowly breathe out","Then imagine a calm scene:","You are lying in a quiet valley surrounded by mountains at night.","The air is cool and peaceful.","Everything around you is calm and still.","Focus on the calm scene while breathing slowly.","Day 20 Sleep Trick – The “Breath Counting Drift”","This technique helps the brain drift naturally into sleep.","While lying in bed:","Take slow nasal breaths.","Count each exhale.","Example:","Exhale 1","Exhale 2","Exhale 3","Continue until 10, then start again.","Keep breathing slow and calm.","Why this works","Counting breaths keeps the brain lightly focused, preventing racing thoughts while allowing the body","to drift into sleep.","It creates a gentle mental rhythm that supports sleep onset.","Day 20 Goal","Allow the body to transition into sleep naturally and effortlessly, reinforcing the strong sleep habits","built over the past 20 days.","By Day 20 many people notice:","falling asleep almost automatically","deeper and longer sleep cycles","improved morning energy"],"completionMessage":"Stay with the practice until your body and mind feel steadier."},{"type":"journal","prompt":"What helped you most on Day 20?","helperText":"Write one or two practical observations.","followUpPrompt":"What will you repeat tomorrow?"},{"type":"close","message":"Day 20 is complete.","secondaryMessage":"You reinforced automatic sleep transition today."}]'::jsonb
